-- SGX Nifty futures turn positive as counting of votes in Indian elections begins
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Thu May 15, 2014 11:01PM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, May 16 (Reuters) - NSE index futures traded on the Singapore Exchange <SINc1> turn positive, surging 0.8 percent after earlier falling 0.6 percent, predicting a near-record-high start for India's NSE index <.NSEI> as vote counting begins.

